message: Always combine items that 'live in the same place' first. Use growth serum on these combined items once or twice, but be careful not to make them 'ultra-grown' as this often leads to negative values. For single ingredients, 'grown' items give positive values, but 'super-grown' or 'ultra-grown' items, especially large ones, often turn negative. Experiment cautiously with the mutation catalyst, but it seemed to yield negative results in my experience. Submit when you have a good 'super-grown' combined item or 'grown' single item, as pushing further often leads to losses.

message: Start by using the Growth Serum repeatedly on base ingredients to make them 'grown', then 'super-grown', then 'ultra-grown'. Combine these grown items, especially those sharing a habitat, for initial value increases. For your most valuable single or combined 'grown' items, use the Mutation Catalyst *exactly twice*. The first mutation will likely create a 'mutant' item with a reduced or negative value, but the *second* application of the Mutation Catalyst to that 'mutant' item will often result in a 'super-mutant' item with a significant score boost (often to 60+). Critically, **DO NOT** use the Mutation Catalyst a third time on a 'super-mutant' item, as this consistently leads to 'corrupted' items with negative values. Also, be cautious with over-applying Growth Serum to single items, as it can eventually lead to negative values.
